AB  - Covid-19 pandemic has severely affected the human lives and businesses around the world. Globally, the demand for hospitality services is at an all-time low due to  borders closing and restricted movement in various countries. This article  highlights the impact of Covid-19 on the hospitality industry, mainly hotels and  restaurants. It further discusses ICT (Information and Communication Technology)  and machine learning-based solutions for the current and future pandemics. The  study has used the exploratory research method. It has referred to the existing  theoretical and empirical findings in the hospitality establishment with regard  to the Covid-19 impact.
